│ 1.  `fcmp ole <negative_snan>, 0.0` evaluates to `false` because `ole` is an "ordered" comparison, and any comparison with a NaN is unordered.                                           │
│ 2.  The `select` instruction therefore returns the false value, which is `%x` (the original negative SNaN).                                                                              │
│ 3.  The optimized code, `llvm.fabs.f16(%x)`, would return a positive SNaN.                                                                                                               │
│ Since a negative SNaN and a positive SNaN have different bit representations, this is a miscompilation.                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This transformation is only valid if we can assume that NaNs are not present, which is what the `nnan` (no NaNs) fast-math flag indicates. The optimization logic should be guarded by a │
│ check for this flag.                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The transformation is likely located in `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp`. I need to find the code that matches the pattern `select(fcmp ole X, 0), -X, X` and add │
│ a check for `hasNoNaNs()` on the `select` instruction.                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Based on my previous analysis of the file, the relevant code is in the `foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs` function. Specifically, the condition at line 2797:                                    │
│ ```c++                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (!Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE)) {                                                                                                               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This handles the `select(fcmp ole %x, 0), -%x, %x` pattern. I need to add `SI.hasNoNaNs()` to this condition to ensure the transformation is only applied when it's safe. The same logic │
│ applies to the other similar transformations in the same function.                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify the file `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp` to add the `SI.hasNoNaNs()` check to the conditions that fold `select` into `fabs`.                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The changes will be:                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ 1.  `if (!Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE))` becomes `if (SI.hasNoNaNs() && !Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE))`.     │
│ 2.  `if (Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT))` becomes `if (SI.hasNoNaNs() && Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT))`.       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This will prevent the incorrect transformation when NaNs must be handled precisely.                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i -e '2797s/if (!Swap/if (SI.hasNoNaNs() \&\& !Swap/' -e '2801s/if (Swap/if (SI.hasNoNaNs() \&\& Swap/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                       │
